<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Wallster</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-02-16 09:38:44</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Like so many others, the quest to get these gloves is very<BR>
simple in and of itself.  It's the faction that's a pain <BR>
in the ass.  To complete the quest, you need to talk to <BR>
the trainer on the top level of the magician's tower in<BR>
the palace of Erudin.  He will ask you something about what<BR>
is the power of the magician or something.  Tell him 'the <BR>
power of summoning'.  He will then ask for two summoned <BR>
daggers and two summoned food.  You give him the stuff, and<BR>
you get your gloves.  You need indifferent(maybe amiable) <BR>
faction to complete the quest.  The most popular way to <BR>
increase your faction is to kill the necromancer that spawns<BR>
near the pier in Toxxulia forrest.  There is an additional <BR>
quest(given by someone else in the same room i think) <BR>
involving some bone pieces that he drops that will get<BR>
you the faction you need as well, but these are lore, so <BR>
you'll have to do some running back and forth.  It shouldn't<BR>
take more than a few iterations to get the faction you <BR>
need.  I haven't done this quest in a long time, so if <BR>
someone who has done it recently could fill in the blanks,<BR>
we'd all appriciate it.  Things like the quest giver's name,<BR>
the necro's name, the bone piece quest giver's name, and the<BR>
necro's level(8?) would be nice.<BR>
<BR>
-Wesko<BR>
Tallon Zek </font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Rutabega</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-18 01:17:20</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>These gloves are basically worthless, and they take a decent chunk of any caster's weight allowance.  But this is the point: they look cool.  The black gloves offset a stark white goss or accent an FBR.  Definitely worth having, if only as a dress uniform of some type.<BR>
<BR>
Like Wallster said, the faction is a pain, but easily attainable if you have a little patience.  Elial Brook, the necro by the docks, is a six minute spawn.  I was a lvl 10 mage, and he conned blue, so I sent in the pet and popped him in the head with a few DD's and ol' Elial dropped quickly.  He usually got only one or two spells off at me, but they're the standard issue necro puffs.  Easy faction - after an hour I could get the gloves.  You need amiable faction, I believe.  I went through the faction with a friend and he had indifferent.  Needless to say, the quest giver laughed at him.  Sorry, I don't know the names of the folks in Erudin.  Just ask around.  it's an easy thread to discover.<BR>
<BR>
Rutabega</font></td></tr></table>
